# Tests

Cutlass treats tests as **production code**: write them deliberately and review them with the same skepticism as feature code.

## Subagents

- **Delegate test authoring** to a subagent (e.g. Task/explore or general-purpose agent scoped to “write tests for X”) so implementation stays focused and test code gets dedicated attention.

## Critical review

After tests land, **review them critically**: gaps (missing edge cases, flaky assumptions, weak assertions), redundancy, unclear failure messages, and mismatches with real behavior or requirements. Reject “coverage theater”; fix or rewrite weak tests instead of merging them unchecked.
